<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-20T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1790: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">William Phillips</persName>, Personal
                                Representative of President Roosevelt in India</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-20T17:00:00-04:00">February
                                    20, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>108. Such comment as has been observed in American press regarding
                            Gandhi’s fast and situation arising therefrom has for the most part been
                            factual and unemotional. Implications involved are probably not
                            appreciated by American public and it is thought that there has been
                            thus far little reaction to existing situation. Censorship in India has
                            undoubtedly greatly restricted possible coverage here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>